observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management strengthen its GAD Focal Point System and require the:

GAD Focal Person to conduct a formal orientation to all individuals who are designated as members of the LGU GFPS including their functions and obligations in order that they can act accordingly and help the LGU in the efficient planning and budgeting for GAD PPAs to properly address gender issues;



GFPS Executive Committee, in coordination with the head of HRMO, to plan and implement an appropriate capacity development program on gender and development for its employees as part of its regular human resource development program;



GAD Focal Person, as the Chairman of GFPS-TWG, to assist in the capacity and competency development and provide technical assistance to the offices or units of the LGU on the actual conduct of planned capacity development program on gender equality and women’s empowerment for the GFPS or LGU employees, as necessary;



GAD Focal Person, as the Chairman of GFPS-TWG, to conduct periodic monitoring and evaluation of the GFPS and undertake measures to address possible issues that may affect the performance of their functions in accordance with the MCW and other GAD-related laws, policies and plans.

We recommended that Management:

Instruct the BAC Secretariat to ensure the following in all of LGU procurements:

•	That the date when supplier signs the PO is always indicated;
•	That the PO shall always include complete details and/or information; 


Direct the Municipal Accountant to require the requesting departments and committees involve in the procurement process of goods to ensure that all the necessary details in the PO and its supporting documents are correctly stated before submitting the documents for processing of payment; and


Direct the Supply/Property Officer and Inspectorate Team to properly accomplish the AIR.

We recommended that Management:

Instruct the BAC to adopt the 6th Edition of PBDs and use the prescribed standard forms for new procurements;


Direct the BAC, Technical Working Group and Secretariat to keep abreast of updates on government procurement policies and attend seminar/training conducted by the GPPB to reappraise themselves on updates on the procurement law;


Direct the BAC to adhere on the timeliness of award of contract to the winning bidder to avoid unnecessary delays; and


Instruct the BAC Secretariat to adopt the updated format of NTP without stating the unnecessary clause granting additional 10 calendar days to implement infrastructure projects or deliver goods.

Instruct the BAC to update/revise the RFQ form to include the suppliers PhilGEPS registration number and require the suppliers to supply said information along with their price quotation;



Instruct the BAC to require from the supplier its Mayor’s Permit/ Business Permit in the use of alternative method of Shopping; and


Instruct the Municipal Accountant to see to it that all disbursements involving the procurement of goods and services undertaken through alternative method of procurement are duly supported with complete documentary requirements.

